## 5. PROPOSED STACK (starting point, not locked in)

- **Backend:** FastAPI (Python) — async by default, which matters since AI media analysis calls can take seconds and shouldn't block the server. Auto-generated API docs also make the future mobile app a clean consumer of the same API. (Alternative considered: Django — more batteries-included, but heavier than needed for an inference-heavy service.)
- **Frontend (website):** Next.js — leaning toward this over plain React/Vite because SEO and discoverability matter for a public education platform; server-side rendering helps content get found via search from day one.
- **Database:** PostgreSQL — structured and queryable, better long-term fit than Firebase for tracking scan history, confidence scores, and multi-language content, even though Firebase would be faster to bootstrap.
- **AI/media analysis layer:** A separate internal service, called via API rather than imported directly into backend routes — keeps it swappable as models improve and lets it scale independently since it's the resource-heavy part. Start by wrapping existing deepfake/AI-detection models or APIs rather than training custom models (that's a v2+ problem).
- **Hosting:** Railway or Render for MVP — cheap and simple. Migrate to AWS/GCP once there's real traffic; don't over-build infra before there's a reason to.

Challenge any part of this stack if a better fit exists for the actual constraints (cost, my skill level, low-end device/bandwidth users) — don't treat it as final.

